						<summary>

						<p>Two sides of a slab set up in front of the well called Pustaka-tīrtha.</p>						

						<p>1369-70 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This badly damaged record seems to register a gift, made over to Bīru-seṭi, son-in-law of Sōmi-seṭi and Doḍatale-seṭi. It reforms to an <hi rend="italic">atikāri</hi> and to god Kaitiladanātha (?).</p>						

						</summary>
